        <LEXMeaning Id="000765001001000" IsBiblicalTerm="M" EntryCode="74.23" Indent="0">
          <LEXDomains>
            <LEXDomain>Able, Capable</LEXDomain>
          </LEXDomains>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-08-17 12:32:26" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a state of incapacity to do or experience something</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>incapacity</Gloss>
                <Gloss>weakness</Gloss>
                <Gloss>limitation</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>A literal rendering of this expression in {S:04701200900042} may not be meaningful, and in fact can be quite misleading. δύναμις is best interpreted as ‘God’s power’ and ἀσθένεια as the weakness which Paul experienced. Therefore, one may be able to translate as ‘my power is greatest when you are weak’ (see Today’s English Version).</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
